[{"id":27645,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["alkylated product with ortho and para&nbsp;substitution.","secondary amine after acidic treatment.","an amide product.","positively charged nitrogen at benzene ring."],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Aniline does not undergo Friedel-crafts reaction&nbsp;due to salt formation with aluminium chloride, the Lewis acid, which is used as a catalyst, whereas&nbsp;aniline is a strong base. So, an acid-base reaction will take place. Thus, aniline reacts with <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math> to form a salt.<br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/75d7b7ac-4e45-493a-91c6-85fa0ddc3273-9711822.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 157px;\" /><br />Due to the positive charge on the nitrogen atom (shows <math><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> effect and it is meta directing), electrophilic substitution in the benzene ring is deactivated. Hence, the Friedel-Crafts reaction will not take place in aniline.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27625,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["D","A","B","C"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/O_8Io7VV57ec8Mhu_ZEhR2PDOMMFJIVMD-assmasFTQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br />C.B. of terminal alkyne will be sp hybridisation and loculised. In other C.B. will be resonance stablised.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27667,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/efde76c4-7004-456c-bfce-cb18582c0d04-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 180px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2daa01ac-d9f7-4bf9-a0e1-5a5eac225898-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 183px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9e7cbecb-8060-400e-a4ff-aea82c71e724-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 180px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/849f3c77-4a7e-4f2b-aaa6-6e61e4304399-image.png\" style=\"width: 260px; height: 187px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1541dfbe-bcb2-4a7c-bd27-dc2e3c180a98-image.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 271px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27635,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/14d9c468-f21c-42de-9220-a2b609f24fed.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 156px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c7b403d1-ddae-4a9e-aaf5-f70d86a78d4d.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 111px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e6884dcf-f016-4c6b-9661-bcc32ecda062.png\" style=\"width: 249px; height: 240px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/08ee4d77-5310-4c7c-b87a-ef73d15176c8.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 138px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><strong>Freidel-Crafts Acylation:</strong></p><ul> <li>Friedel-Crafts acylation reaction is a type of reaction where an acyl group is added to an aromatic ring.</li> <li>This reaction occurs in the presence of an acid chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>Cl</mi></math> and a Lewis acid catalyst like Aluminium chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>AlCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</li> <li>Friedel-Crafts acylation reaction, changes the aromatic ring into a aromatic ketone.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de8f3d55-e97a-44e6-8539-3bf23280d899.png\" style=\"width: 704px; height: 521px;\"/></li></ul>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27639,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/39c1e85b-cc77-47b8-9509-33046aee8348-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 143px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6ae73b4d-ac46-49db-a8ed-a07ad83d8189-image.png\" style=\"width: 248px; height: 150px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a7a995b2-3858-4c56-98a0-7cf433aedf36-image.png\" style=\"width: 248px; height: 131px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/faa48d79-06f6-40e5-bdec-262b38be2c9b-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 102px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>In the first step bromine attacks the carbon-carbon double bond by electrophilic addition reaction mechanism and forms the bromonium&nbsp;cyclic intermediate. In the presence of sodium bicarbonate carboxylic acid group present in the reactant&nbsp;converts to carboxylate ion. This carboxylate ion opens the cyclic bromonium ion ring and forms the desired product.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bdaeac43-97bd-4440-b424-f4895151620b-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 228px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27657,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaBH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","Alkaline <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HCl</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>Zn</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>Hg</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;in presence of acidic medium shows oxidation reaction.&nbsp;</p><p>It converts carbon into acid if carbon is connected to benzene group directly and having at least one hydrogen with it then it can be converted into acid otherwise not. As shown below:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b447cb72-1ac4-4260-ae3f-c65b174dfe44-image.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 253px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27693,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["propanoic acid and ammonium salt","ethanoic acid and ammonium salt","methylamine salt and ethanoic acid","ethylamine salt and methanoic acid"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{~N} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}+\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O} \\stackrel{\\mathrm{H}^{+}}{\\longrightarrow} \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{HCOOH}$. Therefore it gives only one mono chloroalkane.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":27652,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iv</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iv</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iv</mi><mo>)</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iv</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>iii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>(a) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>COOCH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>OH</mi></math> (Hydrolysis of ester)</p><p>(b) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>COOCH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow></mover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>CHO</mi></math> (Reduction of ester)</p><p>(c) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&#8801;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><msub><mi>SnCl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>CHO</mi></math> (Reduction followed by hydrolysis)</p><p>(d)&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1ecc96e1-eabc-41d6-8516-182cdaefd424-image.png\" style=\"width: 435px; height: 90px;\" />&nbsp;(Nucleophillic addition reaction)</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27632,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5XkGtDw71thZ_VUAkwdyqbdjReYa9BdUb3JKmXIoSnk.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3Hye5f99350eA5573bzozF5rEewIQvRGaIM7dsg_Bf8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/wnwMxo_7XA3FT6VJWpCvB64iiEiZJtYeXinASHBeiUw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dXn4czn2gRtAIHpYmFvP3SuNxgRQ6hvGALWXIHDMVK4.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":0,"solution":"HVZ Reaction\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/gwyFIaRIgGJbTqI-FY4E_J2RkXLnPGkxuAue8CNGQ8w.original.fullsize.png\"><br />SECTION - B","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27662,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ef1274b-bc04-4d37-abe6-b5c37edce7ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 127px; height: 89px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9ef72861-a33d-40c7-98c6-eb7ba4414b8f-image.png\" style=\"width: 157px; height: 78px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a3e9f6a-ac83-42fd-b27a-b9009f5f7e8d-image.png\" style=\"width: 132px; height: 92px;\" />","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>RO</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CMe</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Esters are hydrolysed in basic medium(saponification)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27690,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOC}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5+\\mathrm{NaCl}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{COONa}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCl}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}+\\mathrm{NaOH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":27694,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COCl}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CHO}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CHCOOH}$","$\\mathrm{ClCH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/RnKOv31ZXIAr5RihYMyaBE3hQ_f5se7UqkY3V62OVnE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":27675,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bd4fe45d-edd3-41cf-81fd-9426eb480b2c-image.png\" style=\"width: 253px; height: 84px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a6bf07c-1cdd-4efc-9e85-d7a49c35f7f6-image.png\" style=\"width: 205px; height: 109px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8079f788-2eea-4888-b7e7-b0b87738ec06-image.png\" style=\"width: 165px; height: 118px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/85f14677-163d-47cb-8f55-e9c3d