":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27671,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math> convert ester into alcohol by reduction, it does not reduce <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></math> bond between carbon atoms.<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/357f8ad0-6dc7-4e2a-b979-7f3cabea8072-image.png\" style=\"width: 804px; height: 90px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27672,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>","<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>In the mentioned structures&nbsp;<math><msup><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> will get added to the carbon having slight positive charge.<br /><br />Presence of <math><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>l</mtext></math> increases the positive charge whereas an electron donating group like <math><mtext>N</mtext><msub><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> decreases the tendency.<br /><br />Rate of reaction <math><mo>&#8733;</mo></math> <math><mo>-</mo><mtext>M</mtext></math> or <math><mo>-</mo><mtext>I</mtext></math> group<br /><br />Rate of reaction <math><mo>&#8733;</mo></math> <math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mtext>M</mtext></mrow></mfrac></math> and <math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mtext>I</mtext></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />Hence, the correct order will be:<br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b5c0226c-a62e-42a7-8d33-561f2092b726-image.png\" style=\"width: 565px; height: 141px;\" /></p><p><img height=\"142\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e8c61ef6-c2c1-4121-8e4b-9a055c04bd3f-image.png\" width=\"450\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27647,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>63</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>104</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>142</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f0ff0b80-bcb0-4fab-a066-6d3a09d469a4-image.png\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 90px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1da264d8-5cf1-48df-999e-258094014a22-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 209px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c8af080a-a5ba-430a-b3fa-e182e19e2d23-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 75px;\" />C is a para isomer.</p><p>The melting point of para-isomer is comparatively&nbsp;higher than the corresponding&nbsp; ortho and meta-isomers , because of more&nbsp;symmetrical nature; it&nbsp;fits into crystal lattice more readily&nbsp;and so, close packing of molecules in crystal lattice increases the intermolecular force of attraction between molecules.</p><p>Hence&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;has highest melting point that is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>142</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27665,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow></mrow></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math> is very selective and usually used to reduce acid into alcohol.</p><p>Borane is commonly used for the reduction of carboxylic acids in the presence of esters, lactones, amides, halides and other functional groups. In addition, borane rapidly reduces aldehydes, ketones, and alkenes.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27648,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>MnO</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaBH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>When benzoic acid is heated with formic acid in presence of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Mno</mi></math>, benzaldehyde is obtained.</p><p>The reaction is given below, along with benzaldehyde, carbondioxide and water are also obtained.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>HCOOH</mi><munderover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>Heat</mi><mi>MnO</mi></munderover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mi>CHO</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27668,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c86c2604-2ed7-42fa-95c6-5555ed885721-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 87px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5f55fc5b-8b17-48b5-a19b-0a957eb535d2-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 94px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c68ca53f-1183-428c-880b-9b3f793be83b-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 138px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed90ecfb-136c-4380-a3b1-ba3e80ca5e16-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 74px;\" /><br />as <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> is a better nucleophile than <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27623,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["benzoic acid","benzoic acid and aniline","benzoic acid and chlorobenzene","chlorobenzene and aniline"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Xx9UZ-Pv7pMWFBCU1sEMG6ijlYWr71Yyh26ds--l7gs.original.fullsize.png\"/><br />Organic layer in funnel are mixture of chloro benzene and aniline","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27628,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$6$","$3$","$5$","$4$"],"answer":2,"solution":"The compounds having benzylic hydrogen will give benzoic acid on treatment with hot KMnO 4 .\nWhich are following:\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/giRRYQZYGv46-yd_KvyYqpocq4YJwsxi5pXLFwa1Kds.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27686,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["benzophenone","acetophenone","benzoic acid","benzyl alcohol"],"answer":2,"solution":"Any aliphatic carbon with hydrogen attached to it, in combination with benzene ring, will be oxidized to benzoic acid by $\\mathrm{KMnO}_4 / \\mathrm{H}^{+}$.\nHence, (C) is correct.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":27650,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3c6661f2-a5d2-4615-a73e-da4c4be666f1-67f8c20e-d492-410c-bed9-f0fb2bea1948-image.png\" style=\"width: 429px; height: 72px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/30e0e91e-6261-4879-b0cc-1b21fb009ed8-image.png\" style=\"width: 492px; height: 45px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/82f54392-b390-455c-860a-ab7388c5ced3-779c9799-85f0-4040-8160-0b1cfa14df47-image.png\" style=\"width: 402px; height: 46px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7244ae75-8c6b-49ee-8a0c-549e2592b9d7-image.png\" style=\"width: 410px; height: 50px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/71fedead-2724-448d-b2e6-d2cad180ab1e-image.png\" style=\"width: 624px; height: 124px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27633,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Major product B is $\\rightarrow$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uDQz7Od7wcNvPL5SEFlPOYKdUmi9Ys-ewMJDxeJAxIs.original.fullsize.png\"><br />Total number of $\\pi$ bonds in $B$ are 5","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27651,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Mg</mi><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> dry ether <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>Heat</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>OH</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>OH</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>COCH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>OI</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mi>Mg</mi></mover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>MgBr</mi><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></mover><munder><mrow><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>Butanoic</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>acid</mi></mrow></munder></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27644,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/668ce3ce-2388-4c15-9278-b1d11b49d774-image.png\" style=\"width: 288px; height: 100px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8e8e7a64-b2dd-44c8-8317-2f3b163963a5-image.png\" style=\"width: 215px; height: 120px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CHBr</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3224c753-b644-4cf5-ad0b-a9b19eb2ee34-image.png\" style=\"width: 84px; height: 120px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a6646ac4-6585-4b91-b897-613471f0e720-image.png\" style=\"width: 85px; height: 120px;\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CHBr</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Based on the percentage composition of the elements given the molecular formula of the compound is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>8</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>9</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi></math></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fc1671c4-65f6-42ef-9f4b-924a0c4a6842-dbe.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 156px;\" /></p><p>And the degree of unsaturation or double bond equivalent of&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>8</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>9</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi></math>&nbsp;is 4.</p><p>It is mentioned that A is optically active and gives pale yellow precipitate with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>AgNO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</p><p>Hence, the structures of A and B can be deduced based on the following reactions.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1cfc77f5-782b-4944-9836-8f18e2d22e25-13-7-20223.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 378px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27684,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9c7283c3-2dd8-42ca-b561-61a2f3b4dfb0-image.png\" style=\"width: 182px; height: 78px;\" />","<math> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mtext>COOH</mtext> </mrow> </math>","<math><mrow>  <msub>          <mtext>CH</mtext>        <mn>3</mn>  </msub>  <mtext>COOH</mtext></mrow></math>","<math><mrow>  <msub>          <mtext>CH</mtext>        <mn>3</mn>  </msub>  <msub>          <mtext>CH</mtext>        <mn>2</mn>  </msub>  <msub>          <mtext>CH</mtext>        <mn>2</mn>  </msub>  <mtext>COOH</mtext></mrow></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ammonia reacts with carboxylic acid to form ammonium carboxylate (B). Which on heating form amide (C). Amide on reaction with bromine and KOH&nbsp;undergo Hoffmann Bromamide reaction to form amine with one carbon less.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><munder><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mo>|</mo><mo>|</mo></mrow></munder></mover><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>OH</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow></mrow></mover><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><munder><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mo>|</mo><mo>|</mo></mrow></munder></mover><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>&#8854;</mo></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>&#8853;</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><munder><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mo>|</mo><mo>|</mo></mrow></munder></mover><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>&#8854;</mo></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>&#8853;</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi></mover><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><munder><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mo>|</mo><mo>|</mo></mrow></munder></mover><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><munder><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mrow><mo>|</mo><mo>|</mo></mrow></munder></mover><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable><munderover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>Hoffmann</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>bromamide</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>degradation</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>Br</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>KOH</mi></mrow></munderover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (07 Apr)","image":null},{"id":27680,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["(i) $\\mathrm{NaBH}_4$, (ii) Raney $\\mathrm{Ni} / \\mathrm{H}_2$, (iii) $\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}$","(i) $\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4$, (ii) $\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}$","(i) $\\mathrm{B}_2 \\mathrm{H}_6$, (ii) $\\mathrm{DIBAL-H}$, (iii) $\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}$","(i) $\\mathrm{B}_2 \\mathrm{H}_6$, (ii) $\\mathrm{SnCl}_2 / \\mathrm{HCl}$, (iii) $\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/DqPDNn_rT2INu968wTx25q8PxzHtySEZCcbtVk5tVr8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null}]